==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun|cirrhos|es}}

# {{pathology}} A chronic disease of the [[liver]] caused by damage from [[toxin]]s (including [[alcohol]]), metabolic problems, [[hepatitis]] or nutritional deprivation. It is characterised by an increase of fibrous tissue and the destruction of liver cells.

